window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Often, people from broken families become very attuned to the needs of others, especially our parents and siblings. We become skilled at being what people want us to be. In the end, we often lose ourselves and our ability to articulate what we need and want.</p><p>In this episode, we discuss that problem as well as:</p><ul><li>How normal was strange and strange was normal for our guest growing up</li><li>Why he became motivated to break the generational cycle of divorce in his family</li><li>How he felt like burden in his relationships, which made him feel the need to earn love and constantly prevent it from ending any moment</li></ul><p><br></p><p><b>Share your story</b></p><p><br></p><p><b>Shownotes</b></p>"; 
